Absolutely flawless and a pleasant surprise. The food was fresh, well prepared and packaged. The portions were substantial and deliciously flavorful. detailedReviews.author: Evie Harper
detailedReviews.text:
We are from Vancouver BC and are often less than excited about sushi and seafood in Las Vegas. But I saw an ad for this place on Instagram and decided that it was worth the drive over to Summerland to go and check it out. It did not disappoint!
The seafood was probably the freshest and best tasting we have had in Vegas ever! Will definitely be back again
Pokey bowls are full. The avocado bomb was a unique concept. I have yet to see anywhere else. Presentation wise, exquisite.
Staff were polite and helpful. Service wise, efficient and timely. Prices are reasonable and better than anywhere else I‚Äôve seen in the area.
Solid 10 out of 10

detailedReviews.author: Mauro Lopez
detailedReviews.text: We came to enjoy the Monday night game between the RAIDERS and PACKERS. We are from California and love sushi. We we‚Äôre told about this place called ‚ÄúOn Demand Sushi‚Äù on Hualapai in Summerlan. Despite being a small space the food and service is AWESOME. We had a server named Adrianna who was very knowledgeable and friendly. Great personality and very attentive. We had 2 boats of sushi and ordered a teriyaki bowl for one in our party. Overall a great experience and would recommend this location to all our friends.

detailedReviews.author: L Urban
detailedReviews.text: First time to come here. It's a little place, maybe 6-8 tables but they have a big menu. You order at the cashiers and pay first. Food was fast and we had the lovely cashier as our server. She was very nice.

detailedReviews.author: Kurt Baker
detailedReviews.text: We eat here at least twice a month the food and service is always incredible!

detailedReviews.author: Michelle
detailedReviews.text:
This is a real gem. Has a very high ratio of quality to price. Tastes like very expensive sushi but the price is good.

We talked to the owner. You can see an interview with him online (On Demand Sushi Interview with owner and entrepreneur Carey Parriott). He is very careful to make the rice properly, import it from Asia, cook it with the right amount of water for that particular batch of rice, etc. The rice is truly amazing in this sushi. I could eat tons of that sushi rice.

He also does some things differently from many of the cheap sushi joints in Vegas -- trying to make sushi better and give a better product. They have very fresh fish despite being an affordable sushi place.

If you get 5 or 8 items, (platter) you get 15% discount on all the rolls/sashimi/etc.

They have gluten-free non-GMO San-J tamari available at this location. I'm allergic to lots of soy tamari, but this non-GMO one is fine for me.

I believe the wasabi is also gluten-free from looking at the ingredients label (horseradish, corn, maltodextrin, and coloring, so not real wasabi). I think they have fresh actual wasabi available if you ask for it (might be an extra charge).

Some of our favorite rolls are salmon skin maki and Spicy crab. Everything we've had has been good. you can get rolls for under $5 so it's not hard to justify stopping by frequently.

detailedReviews.author: Ashton Diaz
detailedReviews.text: Really delicious sushi and great service

detailedReviews.text: Best sushi I have found on this side of town. It is a regular stop for me.

detailedReviews.author: Ming Ming
detailedReviews.text:
Shocking quality and excellence!
I purchased a meal package that offers great value. The sushi is incredibly delicious, the fish is very fresh, and the sauces are tasty too! The only downside is that the fried calamari doesn't match the picture. It's not the Japanese or Italian style of fried calamari; it's just regular American-style calamari rings. Also, I hope they can introduce meal packages at different price points. That would make it perfect!

detailedReviews.text: First time we went to On Demand Sushi we were blown away.  We were surprised by how small the place was but they were able to accommodate us and the food and service was outstanding.  We‚Äôve gone back many times since, as well as ordered for delivery, and we‚Äôve never been disappointed.  Outstanding!

detailedReviews.author: Brian Thomas
detailedReviews.text:
I only ordered from them for the first time because I just really wanted sushi. I give 1 star because I expect real crab in crab rolls. if you're going to use imitation crab, make sure you specify across all platforms which rolls use imitation crab. And only offering one 2oz container of teriyaki sauce for a teriyaki chicken plate where you didn't marinade before or base during cooking is disrespectful to your customers.

For reference, I ordered the 8 roll platter and teriyaki chicken plate, all of which totaled about $100. What this has taught me is I have to vet all my sushi places better. Based on the first impression, I'm not coming back

detailedReviews.author: Allison Jo
detailedReviews.text: Great value! I got a 5-item platter, poke nacho and yakiniku combo. All delicious! White fish sashimi was not the freshest but it was fine. I'll be back.

detailedReviews.author: Ruth Kindig
detailedReviews.text: Cutest place with amazing sushi! Love that the dining area has a nice and fancy eat-in feel even for the small space/take out vibe!

detailedReviews.author: Todd Kennedy
detailedReviews.text: Tried several weeks ago and have been back many times! Fresh and delicious!

detailedReviews.author: Adrian Barragan

detailedReviews.author: Blayne Sheffield
detailedReviews.text: Great quick place for sushi, always delicious and reasonably priced.

detailedReviews.author: Leah Longoria-Vargas
detailedReviews.text: Very fast and delicious sushi! Vegetarian options are surprisingly plentiful and delicious.

detailedReviews.author: C T
detailedReviews.text: The food is great and I met the owner who was super friendly. I highly recommend On Demand Sushi.

detailedReviews.author: Taritamai Lim
detailedReviews.text:
I was extremely dissatisfied with their combo platter. I read people‚Äôs reviews that their portion sizes are good and you get a lot for your money‚Ä¶well I beg to differ. I ordered their 10 rolls combo party platter. Yeah sounds like a lot except it‚Äôs not when you‚Äôre just ordering sashimi. They really only had 3 varieties of fish (not including the octopus and eel) and it‚Äôs only 4 pieces. Depending on the fish you‚Äôre looking at $13-$14 for 4 pieces. I was hoping they‚Äôd be pretty big pieces for that price, but they are definitely not. It only looks like a lot if you order rolls because of the rice, but honestly with the amount that I paid for that party platter was definitely not worth it. I‚Äôm glad I didn‚Äôt do all sashimi, even though that‚Äôs what my in-laws wanted since they were serving it for their church members at our house. The tray would have looked so empty. I even ordered an extra roll and told them to put it with the rest so that it looks more full‚Ä¶.they did not do that and packed it separately. The large build your own party platter started at $125 plus extra up charge for certain rolls and sashimi fish. With tip, all in all it was roughly $150. I‚Äôll post a picture of the food and you guys can decide if it was worth it. I was trying to feed roughly around 12 elderly Koreans with this fish. Thank goodness I made other food or else this would not have been enough. I‚Äôm sorry, but I will not be ordering from this place again. The only reason why I gave it two stars instead of one was because despite the amount, the ones who did get to eat it said it was good.
Also at the time (on Tuesday 2/21) their online ordering process was having issues and would not complete my order so I ended up having to call the place twice.
